               </msPart>
               <msPart xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part2" n="2">
                  <msIdentifier>
                     <altIdentifier type="partial">
                        <idno>MS. Heb. e. 23/2</idno>
                     </altIdentifier>
                  </msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part2-item1">
                        <locus from="8a" to="9b">Fol. 8</locus>
                        <title>From <persName>Qirqisani</persName>'s כתאב אלאנואר.</title>
                        <note>The end of the thirtieth chapter; the thirty-first, and the greater part of the thirty-second chapter of a Karaitic (?) ritual treatise in Arabic. <p>Chap. xxx ends <quote type="end">נרגע אלאן אלי אסתתמאם אלקול פי אלצרעת</quote>; the following words occur in it: <quote>וקד ואפקה בנימין פי דלך וזעם</quote>.</p>
                           <p>Chap. xxxi begins <quote type="beg">פי אלתיאב ואלגלוד ק̇ והבגד כי יהיה בו</quote>.</p>
                           <p>Chap. xxxii begins <quote type="beg">פי טהר אלמצורע קד כנא קלנא אן לפט̇ה טהרה פי אלכתא̇</quote>.</p>
                        </note>
                        <textLang mainLang="jrb"/>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <p>Syr. Kar. char.; 4to, <material>paper</material>, partly obliterated.</p>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                     <acquisition>Bought through the Rev. <persName>G. J. Chester</persName>, <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1890">1890</date> (from the Genizah).</acquisition>
                  </history>
               </msPart>
               <msPart xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part3" n="3">
                  <msIdentifier>
                     <altIdentifier type="partial">
                        <idno>MS. Heb. e. 23/3</idno>
                     </altIdentifier>
                  </msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part3-item1">
                        <locus from="10a" to="11b">Fol. 10</locus>
                        <title>Fragment of a treatise on גט, in Arabic</title>
                        <note>
                           <locus from="11a" to="11b">Fol. 11</locus> (which seems to belong to the treatise, although the writing is more spaced than on <locus from="10a" to="10b">fol. 10</locus>) begins with the thirty-fourth chapter, beg. <quote type="beg">אלקול פי טלאק אלמסכת פנקול אן אלמסכת אלדי לא יקדר עלי אלכלאם פאשאר אלי אלשהוד אשארת</quote>; it is not by a Karaitic author, although the words <quote>עלי אלאהל אלתלמוד</quote> occur.</note>
                        <textLang mainLang="jrb"/>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <p>Syr. curs. char.; 8vo, <material>paper</material>.</p>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                     <acquisition>Bought through the Rev. <persName>G. J. Chester</persName>, <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1890">1890</date> (from the Genizah).</acquisition>
                  </history>
               </msPart>
               <msPart xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part4" n="4">
                  <msIdentifier>
                     <altIdentifier type="partial">
                        <idno>MS. Heb. e. 23/4</idno>
                     </altIdentifier>
                  </msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part4-item1">
                        <locus from="12a" to="13b">Fol. 12</locus>
                        <title>Fragment of a treatise on logic and grammar (?)</title>
                        <note>a section begins <quote type="beg">צרב תאני והו אן יקול לא תאכל סמכא ותשרב לבנא פלא יכון אלגרץ̇ באלנהי ביאן קבח אלאמרין כמא דכרנא</quote>; the author considers לא (Deut. xxii. 1 and 3) equivalent to באלתקדיר כי) כי).</note>
                        <textLang mainLang="jrb"/>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <p>Syr. squ. char.; 8vo, <material>paper</material>.</p>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                     <acquisition>Bought through the Rev. <persName>G. J. Chester</persName>, <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1890">1890</date> (from the Genizah).</acquisition>
                  </history>
               </msPart>
               <msPart xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part5" n="5">
                  <msIdentifier>
                     <altIdentifier type="partial">
                        <idno>MS. Heb. e. 23/5</idno>
                     </altIdentifier>
                  </msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part5-item1">
                        <locus from="14a" to="15b">Fol. 14</locus>
                        <title>Alfasi on מועד קטן</title>
                        <note>ii. 3 (ידוש בפירות) to ii. 4 (לצורך המועד).</note>
                        <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <p>Syr. squ. char.; 8vo, <material>paper</material>, injured.</p>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                     <acquisition>Bought through the Rev. <persName>G. J. Chester</persName>, <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1890">1890</date> (from the Genizah).</acquisition>
                  </history>
               </msPart>
               <msPart xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part6" n="6">
                  <msIdentifier>
                     <altIdentifier type="partial">
                        <idno>MS. Heb. e. 23/6</idno>
                     </altIdentifier>
                  </msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part6-item1">
                        <locus from="16a" to="22b">Fol. 16</locus>
                        <title>A fragment of responsa</title>
                        <note>end of no. 243 to beg. of no. 254; Maimonides is quoted ; no. 254 beg. <quote type="beg">עוד כתב דמותר לתת המרוב שקורין אשיטה בנקב הבוטה</quote>.</note>
                        <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <p>Germ. Rabb. char.; 8vo, <material>vellum</material>.</p>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                     <acquisition>Bought through the Rev. <persName>G. J. Chester</persName>, <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1890">1890</date> (from the Genizah).</acquisition>
                  </history>
               </msPart>
               <msPart xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part7" n="7">
                  <msIdentifier>
                     <altIdentifier type="partial">
                        <idno>MS. Heb. e. 23/7</idno>
                     </altIdentifier>
                  </msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part7-item1">
                        <locus from="23a" to="24b">Fol. 23</locus>
                        <title>Fragment of a sermon (?) in Arabic</title>
                        <note>beg. <quote type="beg">תאלתה לו כאן בס בשהר מערוף ללענצרה כאן יכתב מתל אלדי כתב לגמיע אלעיאד פתובו יא אכותנא</quote>.</note>
                        <textLang mainLang="jrb"/>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <p>Old Syr. Rabb. char.; oblong, <material>vellum</material>.</p>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                     <acquisition>Bought through the Rev. <persName>G. J. Chester</persName>, <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1890">1890</date> (from the Genizah).</acquisition>
                  </history>
               </msPart>
               <msPart xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part8" n="8">
                  <msIdentifier>
                     <altIdentifier type="partial">
                        <idno>MS. Heb. e. 23/8</idno>
                     </altIdentifier>
                  </msIdentifier>
                  <msContents>
                     <msItem xml:id="MS_Heb_e_23-part8-item1">
                        <locus from="25a" to="26b">Fol. 25</locus>
                        <title>Fragment of the Midrash Thanhuma or Yelamdenu</title>
                        <note>sections בא, שלח and beg. of יתרו, differing from the old editions as well as from that of S. Buber.</note>
                        <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>
                  <physDesc>
                     <p>Syr. squ. char.; 4to, <material>vellum</material>.</p>
                  </physDesc>
                  <history>
                     <acquisition>Bought through the Rev. <persName>G. J. Chester</persName>, <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1890">1890</date> (from the Genizah).</acquisition>
                  </history>
               </msPart>
